<br>
Some of those I see..  But why would a raid leader say (in general) Ok between the paladin and the mage.. um.. ditch the mage.  What would the paladin have that would make him that much more perferred?<br>
<br>
Say it's a super long fight and the paladin can dish out more damage than the epic.  Then perhaps..  But thats situational isn't it?  Even then if the paladin dies he has to be ressed.  If the pet dies a resummoning is quick and pretty much painless.<br>
<br>
Same argument for rangers.. What do they have?  Decent DPS?  Do they beat us that badly?  Do they beat us at all?  Is it in like 90% of situations?  (lol forget they have that archery crap for a sec.)<br>
<br>
Monks.. they can FD pull an do pretty good damage and they do way more than mages?  I mean is it fair to say in almost all raid count situations monks would be perferred?  And if so why?  All you really need is one monk.<br>
<br>
Warriors... geez..  One to three main tanks at most is enough.   Would you ever pick them for the damage?  Seriously?  And again why?  Why the heck would you ever pick them over a mage if theres one there already?<br>
<br>
I mean I know you have a point Jaytee.  If asked to go to an encounter I get.. &quot;ok this mob needs a lot of nukers..&quot; and if necros, clerics, and enchanters can now beat us out as well as druids it's fairly silly.<br>
<br>
But most of those classes you listed don't really have a unique role.  Well at least nothing that only one of them could do just fine, and no more than we do.<br>
<br>
I admit I'm worried about DD status in PoP too, but I'm also eager to see how everything balances out.<br>
<br>
Am I missing that nukes + pets over a long time is less than even warrior melee damage?   I'm personally fine with that.. However.. if this isn't ok then whats the use for wizards?   Theres no way over a long period of time they can maintain their impressive DPS.<br>
<br>
So I'm just wondering how you measure all this up, and what unique abilites these other classes have where a number greater than one would be taken over a mage?<br>
<br>
I also renew the challenge to come up with ideas as well.  I mean if you think somethings missing, please at least suggest some sort of solution.  It doesn't have to be a right one, but the effort is worth just as much as the explaination of the problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#333333>(10/14/02 9:48:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=373.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just thinking</span><hr size=1> I actualy got questions for Jaytee (or someone else). How big is the problem with extra lag due to pets? Would it help with an option to show graphics for [none/own/group/all] pets? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uylaine76.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1095<br> <font color=#333333>(10/14/02 3:35:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=373.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just thinking</span><hr size=1> Unless you got like an anicent computer lag caused by pets just dont exist, some like to think it causes lag but it really doesnt.  Atleast from all the time i've played EQ anyway <p><a href="http://www.bladesofwrath.com">
